Book of Hours, Use of Coutances

Free Library of Philadelphia, Lewis E 90. Rouen?, France, Third quarter 15th century. This manuscript is a book of hours, Use of Coutances, probably made in Rouen in the third quarter of the fifteenth century.  It is illuminated with five three-quarter page miniatures and floral borders in the calendar and on pages for major text divisions.
